name: 16S rRNA (cytosine967-C5)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + cytosine967 in 16S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 5-methylcytosine967 in 16S rRNA
comment: The enzyme specifically methylates cytosine967 at C5 in 16S rRNA.

references.title: Purification, cloning, and characterization of the 16S RNA m5C967 methyltransferase from Escherichia coli.
Identification of the 16S rRNA m5C967 methyltransferase from Escherichia coli.
The first structure of an RNA m5C methyltransferase, Fmu, provides insight into catalytic mechanism and specific binding of RNA substrate.
